<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">Obama Threatens to Veto $440 Billion Tax Deal <span class="divider"> | </span></span> With negotiators nearing an accord on permanent tax breaks for businesses worth $440 billion over 10 years, President Obama rallied Democratic opposition on Tuesday and promised a veto, The New York Times writes. âThe president would veto the proposed deal because it would provide permanent tax breaks to help well-connected corporations while neglecting working families,â a White House spokeswoman said.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/11/26/business/congress-nears-deal-on-major-business-tax-breaks.html"> NEW YORK TIMES </a></span></p>
